f="/sprinter/" style="color:var(--gold)">Sprinter van wraps →</a></li><li><strong>Ram ProMaster</strong> — Wide-body design with maximum wrap surface area.</li><li><strong>Chevy Express / GMC Savana</strong> — Classic full-size vans with flat panel design.</li><li><strong>Ford Transit Connect</strong> — Compact vans for small business fleets.</li><li><strong>Nissan NV200 / NV Cargo</strong> — Compact and full-size Nissan commercial vans.</li></ul><h2>Lettering vs. Partial vs. Full Van Wraps</h2><p class="body-text"><strong>Vinyl lettering</strong> ($400–$1,200) covers the basics — company name, phone number, website, and license info. Best for businesses just starting out or meeting DOT requirements.</p><p class="body-text"><strong>Partial van wraps</strong> ($1,200–$2,800) add visual impact with graphics on key panels — sides, rear doors, and hood. Partial wraps deliver 60–80% of the visual impact at 40–60% of full wrap cost. <a href="/partial-vehicle-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">Partial wraps →</a></p><p class="body-text"><strong>Full van wraps</strong> ($2,800–$5,200) maximize impressions with complete coverage. Full wraps create the strongest brand presence and generate the most leads per vehicle.</p><h2>Van Wrap ROI</h2><p class="body-text">A single wrapped van in Chicago generates 30,000–70,000+ impressions per day at a CPM of just $0.04–$0.07. Compare that to:</p><ul class="services"><li><strong>Google Ads:</strong> $3.56 CPM — 89x more expensive than van wraps.</li><li><strong>Radio Ads:</strong> $1.78 CPM — 45x more expensive.</li><li><strong>Billboard:</strong> $0.35 CPM — 9x more expensive (and fixed location).</li><li><strong>Van Wrap:</strong> $0.04 CPM — and it moves through your service area daily.</li></ul><p class="body-text">Over a 5-year wrap life, a $3,500 van wrap generates an estimated 30–50 million impressions — delivering a <strong>2,500%+ return on investment</strong>. <a href="/roi/" style="color:var(--gold)">Full ROI analysis 